`Effect.retry(eff, schedule)` by itself retries on *any* failure. That's rarely what you want with a typed error union — some tags are transient (NetErr, Timeout) and should be retried, others are permanent (AuthErr, ValidationErr) and should propagate immediately. `Schedule.whileInput((e) => ...)` lets the schedule see the error value and keep iterating only while the predicate holds — so permanent errors short-circuit the retry loop without any extra `catchTag` plumbing.

```typescript
